The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Washington, Aug. 10: The US Federal Reserve has left the benchmark overnight interest rates unchanged in a zero to 0.25 per cent range. It said it would funnel proceeds from its maturing mortgage bonds into longer-term government debt to support a sputtering economic recovery. The Fed has also renewed its pledge to keep the rates low for a long period.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 10: The government is expected to table a bill in Parliament tomorrow to amend the mining act and pave way for auctioning of coal blocks for captive use.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 10: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee is likely to meet the state GST panel on August 18 to discuss the revised draft of the constitutional amendment bill to allay fears of states vis-a-vis providing veto powers to the Centre.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 10: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee will meet PSU bank chiefs on August 14 and is likely to discuss the impact of the hike in lending rates for existing borrowers following the RBIs monetary tightening steps.                            
	 Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, Aug. 10: BlackBerry maker Research In Motion has won a reprieve from a threatened ban on its messenger texting service by Saudi Arabia, which said progress was being made on addressing its concerns.                                                                                                                          
